page.title: 01An introduction to our area.
page.content: The{12 square kilometre}area which we have surveyed, is an area of the town of{Grimsby.}The area is mostly residential, and agricultural. There is one large council estate, called {Nunsthorpe}included in this area, and several different types of private housing areas. Parts of the land which is now used for{agriculture,}is shortly to be developed into new {housing estates. {Grimsby}is a port at the mouth of the{River Humber.}It was once one of the largest fishing ports in the World. However in recent years the {fishing industry}has declined rapidly. Other industries have taken over as the major employers of the local population.
